<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Borders overlap with line-height</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#propdef-line-height" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="Verify that user agents render boxes in document order and cause borders on subsequent lines to paint over borders and text of previous lines." />
        <style type="text/css">
            #d1
            {
                width: 500px;
                font-size: 2em;
            }
            #s1
            {
                border: blue solid;
            }
            #s2
            {
                border: green solid;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if the green line overlaps the blue line.</p>
        <div id="d1">
            <span id="s1">
                Filler Text Filler Text Filler Text Filler Text
            </span>
            <span id="s2">
                Filler Text Filler Text Filler Text Filler Text
            </span>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>